What is your favorite movie(s)?  
What is your all-time favorite TV show(s)?

I'm slowly, but surely becoming disenchanted with network TV.  This is not to say I am going to go the way of MJP and cancel my satellite TV or anything, but for those times when I have nothing to watch and feel like watching something of substance (as opposed to food tv) or I'm at MJP's land of no subscription TV, I want to have a list of things to check out.

So, help me out, peeps!  Ready.....go!

I desperately need to get my laundry done (and by done I mean by Kay at the laundromat).  I am into the bare bones of work-appropriate, hot weather clothes.

So, since my schedule keeps getting f-ed up, I can't really go until Thursday night to drop it off, which means not back until Friday and hang up stuff still wet until at least Saturday.

So, today I am wearing a dress.  I don't know why I don't wear my dresses to work more often.  Compliments are abounding and I feel dressy (as opposed to sloppy in the same pants/tee rotation). 

And, since I will not have anything to wear that is not presently in my closet until Monday, tomorrow I am wearing pants or a skirt with my last white tee, Thursday I am wearing my brown dress and Friday I am wearing my dress jeans (as I do every Friday) with a tank and short sleeve tie-cardigan.  

Sweet!  Maybe this will help me get these things into the regular rotation to snazz it up a bit without spending money.

This is who I am.  I am messy, lazy and kinda plump.
I was messy, lazy and kinda plump when I started this blog.
I was messy, lazy and kinda plump when I lived "at home."
I was messy, lazy and kinda plump when I graduated from college.
I was messy and lazy in college (wasn't plump yet).
I was messy and lazy in high school.
I was messy and lazy all prior to high school.

I am not going to change.  No one else expects me to change.

I am messy, lazy and kinda plump.  
And I'm also cute (admit it, my dimples make you squee - the ones on my face; not on my ass) and smart and happy.

So, this is me.  Owning who I am.

I am P_D.  I am messy, lazy, kinda plump, cute with dimples, smart and happy.  What's up?

Keep calm.
Remember that all I can control is my reaction to the things/people around me.
Eat well.
Work hard.
Be happy!

From News 12: Long Island: Police are at the Roosevelt Field Mall to deal with unhappy fans after singer Justin Bieber didn't show at an appearance. Seriously, there are helicopters hovering and circling all over the area! ETA: Apparently, there was a ruckus/riot which is why they called the appearance. Parents with their spawn pushing and cutting to see him. His website has a list of "rules" for the appearance. And to the first poster on his blog, perhaps you should spend more time in school learning to spell and less time standing on line to meet celebrities. And now we're listening to one of his songs from his website...oy vey, I'm too old to listen to this.

I've never had a flu shot.  I also do not think I have ever had the flu.  I have never had pneumonia.  I've had 1 asthma attack in 2 years.  I do not take daily medication for asthma.
I know N1H1 and regular flu season is upon us and the media (and people I know) is telling me I OMGHAVETO get a flu shot.
And yet, lots of people are giving me convincing arguments to stick to my no-flu-shot guns.

What's your take?
Do you/did you get your flu shot(s)?
Have you had them before?
Are you over 50?
Under 18?
Around children or people with weak immune systems daily?
Do you have a weak immune system?
Have you had the flu before?
Should I get flu shot(s)?

So....what now?  
He goes off and becomes the Face of Boe?
Is there more?
Will they come back?
Will Baby GwenRhys join Torchwood?
WHAT WHAT WHAT?

I don't think I am amused.  I think I am feeling the way I felt during the last season of Forever Knight...except at least they let me know it was over.  They made it clear to me.  They called the last episode Last Knight.
This?  This leaves me unsettled.  Discontent.
Yeah, I need to get out more.</lj-cut>

Is it bad that now I want to go back to bed?
